Run the local agent-facing proxy on `127.0.0.1:<port>`.

Agent CLIs point at it via `OPENAI_BASE_URL`. The proxy discovers providers, picks the cheapest one for each model, and signs each request.

Usage: soma inference proxy [OPTIONS] --config <CONFIG>

Options:
      --config <CONFIG>
          Path to the proxy TOML config

      --address <ADDRESS>
          Address whose keypair signs the channel; defaults to the keystore's active address

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

EXAMPLE:
    soma inference proxy --config client.toml
